  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nEarlier, geth used to return chainId as 0 when it was not fully synced. With https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/21686 , now it returns an error if it's not past the eip 155 block. Need to handle this error scenario.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse stable, Geth 1.10\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nWe get an `Endpoint NotReachable` error on lighthouse when geth sync is not past the eip 155 block which is misleading.\r\n \r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nShould handle the error case and return Not Synced error message.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nHandle the error case here \r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/9eb1945136cc2e517bed47d7a8a1cb1c6915d23a/beacon_node/eth1/src/service.rs#L162-L164",
