    "body": "@jmcph4 the `EndpointError::FarBehind` implies that the eth1 node is not synced so we can use that instead. \r\n\r\nI think the simplest way to resolve this would be to return a `Eth1Id::Custom(0)` on getting the error message from the eth1 node since we return a `FarBehind` endpoint on getting chainId of 0 anyway\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/9eb1945136cc2e517bed47d7a8a1cb1c6915d23a/beacon_node/eth1/src/service.rs#L167-L174\r\n\r\nYou will have to modify the get_chain_id function [here](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/9eb1945136cc2e517bed47d7a8a1cb1c6915d23a/beacon_node/eth1/src/http.rs#L93) to return a `Eth1Id::Custom(0)` on the specific eip 155 error\r\n\r\nLet me know if you have other questions",
